The paper focuses on the phenomenon of information cascades on social media platforms, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of computer science and social science. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also discusses the engagement and perception of users with cascades, which could fall under cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences). The study of retweet cascades and audience engagement could also fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity and Privacy). Finally, the paper mentions the use of Twitter as a platform, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia).
